# CertifyMe Full Stack Assessment

## Tech Stack
- Flask (Backend)
- SQLite (Database)
- HTML/CSS/JS (Frontend)

## Features
- Admin Signup & Login
- Forgot Password (token-based)
- Session-based Authentication
- Create, View, Edit, Delete Opportunities
- Data Persistence
- User-specific Data Isolation

## API Endpoints

### Auth
POST /signup  
POST /login  
POST /forgot-password  

### Opportunities
GET /opportunities  
POST /opportunities  
PUT /opportunities/<id>  
DELETE /opportunities/<id>  

## How to Run

### Backend
cd backend  
pip install -r requirements.txt  
python app.py  

### Frontend
Open `admin.html` using Live Server

## Database
- SQLite is used
- Database is created automatically when the backend runs

## Notes
- No UI changes were made as per instructions
- All data is stored in the database (no hardcoded data)
- Each admin can only access their own opportunities